#Text=You 've said that you will repeal the EFA , will you draft up a replacement Bill ?
#Text=If so , will you take a bipartisan approach when drafting up a possible replacement ?
#Text=J.K.
#Text=: That is our intention .
#Text=The laws that govern our democratic process are owned by the people , not the group of politicians that happen to occupy the Treasury benches at any one point in time .
#Text=The self serving laws that the current Government put in place are an absolute mess .
#Text=Anyone who wants to take part in the democratic process is being forced to consult a lawyer , and the confusion has paralysed political and third parties for the first part of the year .
#Text=Labour ’s intention was to curb its critics , and in this respect , the Electoral Finance Act has done exactly what Helen Clark hoped .
#Text=National will repeal this legislation and consult other parties on a set of rules which are fair , transparent and promote free speech and open participation in our democracy .
#Text=( (
#Text=WN
#Text=) )
#Text=You 're relatively politically inexperienced compared to your opponent , Helen Clark .
#Text=Do you think the voters will take this into consideration at the voting booth ?
#Text=How does your former career in finance help you in a political setting ?
#Text=How about your childhood growing up in a state-house , among other things ?
#Text=J.K.
#Text=:
#Text=I am proud of my achievements since I have been the leader of the National Party .
#Text=It is true I have not been a career politician , but I believe I bring a fresh approach to politics in this country .
#Text=I am not interested in revisiting the arguments of the 80 ’s and 90 ’s or subscribing to some arcane ideology .
#Text=I believe I am a pragmatist .
#Text=I am interested in what works – not where it has come from or who is promoting it .
#Text=I do n’t trust anyone who believes they have all the answers on everything .
#Text=They are setting themselves up for a rather large fall .
#Text=My career in business taught me a lot about managing people , reaching consensus and taking people with me as we work together for a common purpose .
#Text=In my view , good business leaders listen to the people they serve and fight fiercely to protect those interests .
#Text=In that regard , if I am privileged enough to be elected Prime Minister , I plan to be an unashamed cheerleader for this country on both the national and world stage .
#Text=In reference to my upbringing , I believe I was tremendously lucky .
#Text=I had a mother who set extremely high standards , who pushed us as children and never once tried to limit our ambition .
#Text=Mum taught us that life is what you make it , that there is no dress rehearsal , and unless you make the most of your opportunities you may live to regret that .
#Text=I try to give my kids the same sort of freedom and share with them the same sort of values that my mum gave to me .
#Text=That is , if you work hard and do n’t give up when you hit the hurdles - almost anything is possible .
#Text=Believe in yourself .
